relevant_findings.physical_examination: Patient exhibited inspiratory stridor and severe subglottic stenosis measured at 1.5 cm below vocal cords, with lumen diameter of 4 mm.

physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Blood pressure declined from 150/80 mmHg to 110/60 mmHg during procedure.

relevant_findings.physical_examination: Patient presented tachycardic and hypertensive with initial vital signs showing severe respiratory distress.

physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Heart rate slowed from 120 bpm to 65 bpm while blood pressure declined from 220/120 mmHg to 120/65 mmHg after sedative administration.

relevant_findings.physical_examination: Patient had an artificial upper trachea due to prior traumas, requiring treatment for chronic pain.

physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Patient maintained above 92% oxygen saturation throughout the procedure.
